{{Infobox Diplomatic Mission |name = Embassy of Switzerland in London |location = [[Marylebone]], [[London]] |coordinates = {{coord|51.5185|-0.1608|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |image = SwissEmbassyLondon.JPG |address = 16/18 Montagu Place, London, W1H 2BQ |ambassador = Dominik Furgler }}
The '''Embassy of Switzerland''' (<small>{{lang-de|'''Schweizerische Botschaft im Vereinigten Königreich'''}}, {{lang-fr|'''Ambassade de Suisse au Royaume-Uni'''}}, {{lang-it|'''Ambasciata di Svizzera nel Regno Unito'''}}</small>) in [[London]] is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Switzerland]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/263519/LDL_December_2013.pdf |title=The London Diplomatic List |date=14 December 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211155353/https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/263519/LDL_December_2013.pdf |archivedate=2013-12-11 |df= }}</ref> It consists of a large nineteenth-century building with a modern addition and is located halfway between [[Montagu Square]] and [[Bryanston Square]]. There is a commemorative stone at the entrance to the embassy marking its rebuilding in 1970.
